latestIgtvVideos.caption:
رنجش ہی سہی دل ہی دکھانے کے لیے آ، 
آپھر سے مجھے چھوڑ کے جانے کے لیے آ ۔

اردو کے شہرہ آفاق اور نامور شاعر احمد فراز کا اصلی نام سیّد احمد شاہ تھا۔ وہ ۱۲ جنوری ۱۹۳۱ء کو صوبۂ سرحد کے شہر کوہاٹ میں پیدا ہوئے ۔سینکڑوں خوبصورت اشعار کے خالق، آبروئے غزل، خوابوں کے سوداگر، منفرد لب و لہجہ کے نامور اردو شاعر، احمد فراز کا شمار عہدِ حاضر کے مقبول ترین شعراء میں ہوتا ہے۔ ان کی عمومی شناخت ان کی رومانوی شاعری کے حوالے سے ہے لیکن وہ معاشرے کی ناانصافیوں کے خلاف ہر دور میں صدائے احتجاج بلند کرتے رہے ۔

مہدی حسن نے فراز کی کئی غزلوں کو اپنی آواز کا سحر عطا کیا جس میں ‘رنجش ہی سہی دل ہی دکھانے کے لیے آ’ بہت پسند کی گئی اور آج بھی اس کی مقبولیت برقرار ہے۔
 
ٹیم ایل پی ایس آج آپ کے یوم پیدائش پر آپ کو خراج عقیدت پیش کرتی ہے

Video Credits: Talha Bin Wasi 
Captio Credits: Masood Ahmed

اردو کے مشہور و معروف شاعر، جون ایلیا، ایک قابل تعریف شخصیت کے مالک ہیں۔ انہوں نے نہ صرف اپنی خوبصورت تحریروں سےاردو زبان میں اپنا نام ہمیشہ کے لۓ امر کردیا بلکہ اپنے قلم کے ذریعے طنز و مزاح کو بھی مزید دلچسپی بخشی۔ ساتھ ہی شاعری کا وہ اعلیٰ اسلوب پیش کیا کہ جس کے ذریعے زبان و بیان کے معیارات کا تعؔین کیا گیا۔
ان کی شاعری ہمارے حالات کی بہترین عکاسی کرتی ہے جس میں محبت و خلوص سے لے کر درد و تنہائی تک تمام جذبات نہایت خوبصورت انداز میں قلمبند کیے گئے ہیں۔
ان کی شاعری کے مطالعے سے وہ تمام احساسات ہمارے دلوں میں گردش کرتے ہیں جن سے ہماری شخصیت اور زندگی کی وابستگی ہے۔
آج جون ایلیا کی سالگرہ کے موقع پہ ٹیم ایل پی ایس نے ان کو خراجِ عقیدت پیش کرنے کی یہ معمولی سی کاوش کی ہے۔

Caption credits: Sara Ali

“The evil that men do lives after them; the good is oft interred with their bones.”
-Julius Caesar 

Of the earnest soul in the world of poetry, philosophy and playwright, the bard of avon has inspired our hearts with rhetorical and fervent literature on the genre's of life, love, death, revenge, grief, jealousy, murder, magic and mystery. 

'tis the day that stands in joy and melancholy to be celebrated as his birthday. Shakespeare also died on 23 April; in 1616, when he was 52 years of age as he deciphers in wit; 

“This day I breathed first: time is come round,
And where I did begin there shall I end;
My life is run his compass.”
- Julius Caesar

LPS pays a heartiest tribute to the greatest literary figure we mentor in the world of literature, with the recital of his famous work unveiling the skills of the members of our theatre wing, entrusting the life His words breathe when spoken! 

To all the Shakespeare lovers, let this day encourage us to speak like the Bard and the characters in his plays and celebrate his love.

Indecisive? We bring you the palette to make it easy. Choose your call and let your decision startle you with unleashing the strengths you never knew about. This tenure, be a part of our literary ensemble to resurrect the literary culture we have been longing for. Make sure it doesn’t become a wait until next time!

Apply at the link in bio.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Zaawiya
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Zaawiya, an emotion for sketching your perspective on the hearts of the unknown. To the dreamy literary evenings that NEDUET witnessed back to back like none other! Zaawiya already had an impact on the lives of those who witnessed it and yet again to be witnessed once again, soon.
This January marks two succesful years of our pride filled accomplishment, our very own "Zaawiya". 

We might never put a finger on the exact emotions for describing Zaawiya but we will always be fond of the precious time we spent on it! Thank you to the founders and everyone who made it a real success. To those who miss it, we feel your hearts and those who are naïve to it, embrace yourself to get known.

کیوں تو اچھا لگتا ہے، وقت ملا تو سوچیں گے!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Bae-Wazan Mushaira #1
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Put in a lot of wit, loads of humour and a healthy dose of present-day situation, add years of experience and mix it well with good acting and what do you have?
"Bae-wazan Mushaira"
LPS-NEDUET brings you a light hearted mushaira inspired by the legandary loose mushaira, to loosen your laughter in this difficult time.
We dedicate this episode to the late Moin Akhtar on his 9th death anniversary.

A shoutout to our talented friends Dabeer and Rayyan from NERDS !

#MushairaIdharUdharSe

latestIgtvVideos.title: Tribute to Allama Iqbal
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
تیرے عشق کی انتہا چاہتا ہوں
میری سادگی دیکھ کیا چاہتا ہوں

Today, 21st of April, marks the 82nd death anniversary of the hero who fought with pen, not against the government, but against illiteracy and conservatism. This uncapped hero made it a point that literary arts are the key to firm grounds of any nation. Because Literature is what feeds and cleanses the soul.

This man is Allama Iqbal: an evergreen, literary victor. Come, let us join our prayers, cherish his heroic endeavours, and recite Fateha for Shayar-e-Mashriq, Allama Muhammad Iqbal.
The poem "Tery Ishq Ki Intiha Chahta Hun" taken from his famous poetic collection "Bang-e-Dara".
#SHAHEEN

latestIgtvVideos.caption:

I took the one less traveled by, 
And that has made all the difference." Tributing the golden words of the Poet Laureate of Vermont, Robert Lee Frost (Born 26th March 1874). Focussing on realistic depictions of rural life he examined the complex social and philosophical themes.

No fake applause. No filler lines. Just poets and the kind of words that make you sit up a little straighter.
Our Mushaira isn’t a show. It’s a gathering. And in that space, couplets don’t just rhyme, they cut.
If you’ve ever wanted to feel understood by a stranger on stage, this is where it might happen.

This play, powered by @nomadsadventureservices  isn’t here to entertain you.
It’s here to pull something out of you. Maybe discomfort. Maybe recognition. Maybe both.
Because what happens on stage is never just about the characters. It’s about who you see in them and that epiphany is one of the many feelings the host play aims to evoke.
